title: Oil giant Saudi Aramco made a historic $161 billion profit last year
description: Oil giant Saudi Aramco reported Sunday earning $161 billion last year, claiming the highest-ever recorded annual profit by a publicly listed company and drawing immediate criticism from activists.

title: Israeli forces kill 3 Palestinian gunmen in West Bank
description: Israeli forces shot and killed three Palestinian gunmen Sunday who opened fire on troops in the occupied West Bank, the military said, the latest bloodshed in a year-long wave of violence in the region.

title: Historic ties to Russia but looking to the West, could Georgia be the next Ukraine?
description: The former Soviet state of Georgia is caught between its historic ties to the East and a future that may lie closer to the West.

title: Four astronauts splash down off Florida coast ending 5-month mission
description: Four space station astronauts returned to Earth late Saturday after a quick SpaceX flight home.
